Rating: 4
This is one of our all-time favorites, we make it again and again. We usually experiment: our favorite combinations have red onion rings and marinated artichoke hearts, and we substitute smoked gouda for the mozzarella. Any way you make it, though, it's great!

Rating: 4
This is delicious. I used pesto on the crust, as suggested. It took longer (2 HOURS!) than I had anticipated (for pizza) due to the prep time of the veggies, but it was worth it. I found out that my boyfriend doesn't love a lot of goat cheese, so next time, I will just use a 3oz package. I will definitely make this again, even change it around to incorporate some leftovers in the fridge!

